   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p><milestone unit="passage" n="Pāyantika-dharma 54-55"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><w>kātäk</w><w>praṣtā</w><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>k<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><w>pāssi</w>
<lb corresp="#b5"/><w>wlesaṃsune</w></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">stood ... at a time ... to guard</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">operation (?)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Four fragments of this leaf exist: SHT 4523, SHT 1044 and SHT 1510. Of the first of these, there are two smaller fragments a and b. While a (like 1044 and 1510) was found at Siŋgim, the find spot of SHT 4523 is reported as unknown at the <bibl><title corresp="ref:idp0000"/></bibl> website.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="lingcomment">No TA equivalent of Skt. <hi>gardabha°</hi> 'donkey' can be recognized in the gloss. This is all the more unfortunate, since this word is so far not attested in TA. On the basis of TB <hi>kercapo</hi> /kercə́po/ 'donkey', one would expect TA <hi>*karcäp</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">probably comments on Skt. <hi>gardabhapālipūrvi[ṇ](a)</hi> 'having been a donkey herd before'. This gloss is difficult to read, since several photos were combined, including the facsimile in <bibl><title corresp="ref:sanderandwaldschmidt1985"/></bibl> (plate 7), none of which is sufficiently clear (see <bibl><title corresp="ref:wille2012"/><citedRange>103</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#b5" type="lingcomment"><hi>wlesaṃsune</hi> may be for <hi>wlesatsune*</hi>, an abstract derived from an adj. <hi>wletsats'</hi>, in turn derived from <hi>wles</hi> 'work' (hence Peyrot apud <bibl><title corresp="ref:wille2012"/><citedRange>103</citedRange></bibl> 'Wirksamkeit' ['effectivity']). The relationship of the gloss to the Sanskrit text remains obscure.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">glosses Skt. <hi>methaken=</hi> (instr.sg.) 'bad deed' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:wille1995"/><citedRange>142</citedRange></bibl>). Also for this gloss, the facsimile in <bibl><title corresp="ref:sanderandwaldschmidt1985"/></bibl> (plate 7) is indispensable.</note></p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p><label>Online access</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:idp0000"/></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2014"/><citedRange>166</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:wille2012"/><citedRange>103</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
         </div>
